        rdfs:label                      "GABA modulator";
        rdfs:subClassOf                 obo:CHEBI_38632 , obo:CHEBI_51374;
        obo:IAO_0000115                 "A substance that does not act as agonist or antagonist but does affect the gamma-aminobutyric acid receptor-ionophore complex. GABA-A receptors appear to have at least three allosteric sites at which modulators act: a site at which benzodiazepines act by increasing the opening frequency of gamma-aminobutyric acid-activated chloride channels; a site at which barbiturates act to prolong the duration of channel opening; and a site at which some steroids may act.";
